web|url=http://geonames.usgs.gov|accessdate=2017-12-30|title=US Board on Geographic Names|publisher=[[United States Geological Survey]]|date=1984-07-01}}</ref>\n|blank1_name =\n|blank1_info = \n|website = \n|footnotes = \n}}\n\n'''Hawley''' was a small [[settlement]] in [[Fairfield Township, Russell County, Kansas|Fairfield Township]], [[Russell County, Kansas|Russell County]], [[Kansas]], [[United States]].\n\n==History==\nHawley was issued a post office in 1880. The post office was discontinued in 1909.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kshs.org/geog/geog_postoffices/search/placename:/county:RS|accessdate=2017-12-30|title=Kansas Post Offices, 1828-1961|publisher=Kansas Historical Society}}</ref> The population in 1910 was 33.<ref name=\"Blackmar\">{{cite book | last1 = Blackmar | first1 = Frank Wilson | title = Kansas: A Cyclopedia of State History, Volume 1 | url = https://archive.org/details/kansascyc01blac | location = Chicago  | publisher = Standard Publishing Company | page = [https://archive.org/details/kansascyc01blac/page/831 831] | date = 1912}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Russell County, Kansas}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Former populated places in Russell County, Kansas]]\n[[Category:Former populated places in Kansas]]\n\n\n{{RussellCountyKS-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n|name = Hawley, Kansas\n|settlement_type = \n|nickname = \n|motto =\n\n<!-- Images -->\n|image_skyline = \n|image_caption = \n|image_flag = \n|image_seal =\n\n<!-- Maps -->\n|pushpin_map              = Kansas#USA\n|pushpin_label            =  Hawley\n|pushpin_label_position   = right <!-- the position of the pushpin label: left, right, top, bottom, none -->\n|pushpin_map_caption      = Location within the [[U.S. state|state]] of [[Kansas]]\n|image_map                = \n|map_caption              = \n|image_map1               = \n|map_caption1             =\n\n<!-- Location -->\n|subdivision_type = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n|subdi